Recommended settings:

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 10

  • LORA weight for txt2img: reccomended 0.3-0.7.

  • Keys: ponytail_weave_hairstyle

Very simple to use, just use the keyword, maybe with a 1.3 weight.

As you can see many of my images have a perfect hime cut hairstyle not showing the fronthead, in those images i used my model Long Hime Cut Hairstyle in inpaint, first i generated the images as i wanted with ponytail weave model, then i sent to inpaint, masked the fronthead, checked fill checkbox and wrote in the prompt only this: "(long_hime_cut_hairstyle:1.3),<lora:long_hime_cut_hairstyle:0.5>" and then generated to have a perfect hime cut hairstyle.

Remember if you are inpainting an image after the other that before sending to inpaint your image you have to close the last image from img2img or in the new generation it will remember the old masked part other then the masked part of your new image, doing a mess.

Also many of the images are generated using controlnet poses packs that you can find in my page.

Works also with anime.

Enjoy!

items.name: Invading Executioner - Code Vein
items.description:
Code Vein was a great game with great waifus, among them being best boss girl Invading Executioner, to whom many enraged and pissed-off Revenants died time and time again. However, my deaths to this beautiful woman did not diminish my love for her. Instead, my horny only grew stronger, and so here we are with this tributary lora.

There are 3 versions:

  1. Normal is trained on AnyLora (so it's saturated asf)

  2. Desat is trained on NAI (so it would generate less saturated results)

  3. Free is trained on also NAI, with a diversely tagged dataset in the hopes of making it easier to manipulate the character design. Not sure I really succeeded with that, but it's there if you want it.

TIPS:

  • All three can generate her outfit by itself through weight lowering and removing her descriptive tags, though the outfit itself doesn't have a tag assigned to it.

  • I didn't actually intend for this, but adding "3D" to the prompt makes it much sharper and more detailed.

  • Token is not consistently required, a short description is often enough.

  • Her black scleras (whites of her eyes) are not consistent, I recommend using this lora to keep it frequent.

Tested on both realistic and anime models. Mildly NSFW capable.

Enjoy!

items.name: CityEdge_FusionMix
items.description:
日本語の説明は後半にあります。

This is a 2.5D merged model to realize 'fusion' in various aspects. Because of the complex merging process, I believe you will enjoy the characters and details that only this model can produce.

Specifically, the model has the following 'fusion' features.

  • This model is a 'fusion' merge model of both photorealistic and anime-like models, to create a 2.5D model.

  • Characters will be produced as the 'fusion' of Asian and Western styles.

  • The merging process is complex, and the merged models have unique 'fusion' details that are different from those of other merged models.

The merging process is generally as follows.

First, many photorealistic models are merged. The criteria for selecting models is if they can produce a photorealistic image when outputting a background without people. More than 15 models that meet this criterion are merged, including minor ones. Finally, only chilled remix and epiCRealism have a composition ratio of more than 10%. (A)

Next, a separate animated model is multi-block merged to create a clear, detailed, and descriptive animated model. This is basically the same as the one used in CityEdge StyleMix, and the main models used are: anything v5, Counterfeit v3, hassaku.(B)

Then, the model (B) is multi-block merged with the model (A) to create a 2.5D model. Finally, a thin layer of FaceBombMix, etc. is applied to ensure stability as a 2.5D model.

Both SFW and NSFW outputs are capable. High quality and unique images can be output in a short prompt. VAE is not needed, but you can try some.

List of my models

  • CityEdgeMix : Simple photo-realistic model based on Chilled family

  • CityEdge_ToonMix : Simple 2.5D anime-like model based on CityEdgeMix

  • CityEdge_2dToonMix : Pure 2D anime-like model merging only 2D models

  • CityEdge_StyleMix : Anime-like model with detail depiction by making use of block-merge

  • CityEdge_FusionMix : 2.5D model focusing on unique depiction through merging many models and block-merge.

  • Landscape_Photoreal : Model that produces photorealistic output, whether with characters or just the background

  • CityEdge_DollyMix : Model that produces doll-like and 3D animated movie-like output

さまざまな要素を融合（Fusion）させて作成した、2.5Dマージモデル。非常に複雑なマージプロセスを経ているため、このモデルでしか出せないキャラクターやディテールが楽しめると思います。

具体的には、以下のような特徴を持たせています。

  • 全体の描写は、フォトリアル系をベースにアニメ系を「融合」し2.5D化。

  • 人物描写は、アジア系をベースに欧米系を「融合」しエキゾチックに。

  • 複雑なモデルマージにより他のマージモデルとは異なる独自のディテールを表出。

マージプロセスは概ね以下のようになっています。

最初に、多数のフォトリアル系モデルをマージしています。モデルの選択基準は、人物なしの背景を出力した際にフォトリアルな画像を出せるかどうか。この基準に合致する15以上のモデルを、マイナーなものも含めマージしています。最終的に構成比が10%を超えているものはchilled remixとepiCRealismのみ。(A)

次に、別途アニメ系のモデルを階層マージし、クリアで詳細な描写のあるアニメモデルを作成しています。これはCityEdge StyleMixで利用したものと基本的に同じもので、使用している主なモデルは、Anything v5, Counterfeit v3, hassaku。(B)

そのうえで、(A)のモデルに(B)のモデルを階層マージし2.5D化。最後にFaceBombMix等を薄く重ねて2.5Dモデルとしての安定性を確保しています。

エロと非エロ、どちらにも対応。短いプロンプトで高品位かつ独自性のあるユニークな画像が出力できます。VAEは焼き込み済みですが別のものを使用してもいいと思います。

モデル一覧

  • CityEdgeMix : Chilled系をベースにしたシンプルなフォトリアル系マージモデル

  • CityEdge_ToonMix : CityEdgeMixを2.5D化したシンプルな2.5Dアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_2dToonMix : 2Dモデルだけをマージしたピュア2Dアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_StyleMix : 階層マージを駆使してディテール描写にこだわったアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_FusionMix : 多数のモデルのマージと階層マージによる独自の描写にこだわった2.5Dモデル

  • Landscape_Photoreal : キャラクターがいても、背景だけでも、フォトリアルな出力が得られるモデル

  • CityEdge_DollyMix : ドール調・3Dアニメ映画調の出力が得られるモデル

items.name: Color101 VAE
items.description:
A VAE for generating higher dynamic and more natural image in comparison with the common VAE like 840000, Anything, kl-f8-anime2, etc.

Important note:

This VAE is for SD1.5 only!

This VAE may generate undesirable results on small resolution like 512x512, according to feedbacks. Color101 is more suitable for generating big image directly (that was what I did while tuning this VAE) or using hires fix for larger resolution.

The comparison images are compressed to .jpeg files automatically by Civitai.com, the difference of color shown here would be affected. So, it is better to make comparison by yourself.

Usage:

Put the file inside stable-diffusion-webui\models\VAE.

v1 update:

1. Provide more and clearer detail than most of the VAE on the market.

2. Fix detail distortion.

3. Skin tone is more natural than old version.

v0.1 update:

1. Fix green artifacts appearing in rare occasion.

2. Fix blurry detail.

What is VAE?

A VAE affects image where fine detail like texts and eyes present, at scale, it doesn't. If you look closely at the eyes in the comparison images, the eyes in some VAE sample has lost the slera in eyes. I recommend you that make some sample on your own to see the difference, because the images uploaded here were automatically compressed to .jpeg file with loss.

VAE in SD works as a decoder to calculate the latent space of a pixel for determining what color a pixel should be. The more complex around a pixel, the more factors needed to be decided, so in opposite, if your image structure is simple, it won't be changed drastically.

This Color101 VAE can give your images more vibrant colors, closer to HDR effect, higher saturation and add more redness to skin in comparison to other VAE on the market. If you like thick color, this should be your choice.

You can see https://stable-diffusion-art.com/how-to-use-vae/ for more detail.

How I archived my generations:

  1. txt2img: DPM++ SDE Karras with 20 steps,512x512(can go up to 768 for wide or tall), Restore faces on (using CodeFormer weight 1.0 in Settings), Hires-fix on, to 1024x1024 (double original size) with your preferred upscaler and Denoise 0.5, CFG 7. Then send to img2img!

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

📝Biography📝

🌟Veronica Leal🌟

born on December 17, 1993, in Cucuta, Colombia, is a popular film actress and model. She is known mainly for her acting performances in videos and web scenes. In 2017, at 24 years old, Leal began her career in the entertainment industry with her first shoot for the film studio, Lets-Doeit. She went on to work with several other film studios, including Fake Hub, TMW Network, A.S. Media, and MetArt Network.

Leal has also performed in videos with other famous actresses such as Aislin and Lilu Moon. She has a distinctive figure, standing at a height of 162 cm (5 feet 4 inches) and weighing 47 kg (103 lbs). Her figure measures 32C-22-32, with beautiful blonde hair and brown eyes. She has tattoos on her right flank and right shoulder blade, and her left nostril is pierced.

When not in front of the camera, Leal enjoys spending her free time in nature, hiking, and reading. She is also a dog lover and a swimming enthusiast. Leal maintains a big base of fans on her social media profiles and is active on Instagram under the username Veronica Leal Official.

💡Workflow Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling🔧

  • What's the + for?

    • Just an easy way to indicate the dataset image for this particular LORA was based off a minimum of 1024px+ quality source images with the LORA trained at 1024,1024 (I may go higher in the future if I can get a properly working configuration).

    • For the most part, you can start with higher base resolutions to capture more details and/or generate higher quality outputs. See some of the gallery examples.

    • You don't have to gen at high resolution, low res generations will be better quality as well.

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted @ .75 - 1.1.

  • For photoreal shots, I've found sampling steps best well above 50 give better results.

  • ControlNet is your friend. Embrace the dark side.😈

    • Tile pre-sample and model is good for extreme close ups

    • I use segmentation for lots of my generations now.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • This + series is something new, let me know if I should take the extra time it takes to create these type of LoRAs or just stick with the regular quality.

  • Help me help you: Leave a review if you've used this LORA.

  • Most of my gens are not voodoo or outside of workflows I've indicated here or in my other posts.

    • In other words: Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond with suggestions.

Image was trained on SD1.5, so it is good for most other checkpoints. I would recommend setting the strength to 0.8-1. Highres.fx = VERY YES. I usually go about 1/2 of my initial steps with a denoising strength of 0.3-0.4

Activation word is "motu_sorceress". To get the classic look, use "beautiful woman wearing a blue and white long sleeved v-neck bodysuit, blue and white long sleeved v-neck bodysuit with feather detailing, eagle headdress, orange feather cloak, blue boots with white fur trim". If you leave those out, you get a pretty cool looking if generic superheroine/sorceress. Examples are in the photos.

Good luck, have fun, and stay tuned for more 80's icons!

items.name: James Jean Style
items.description:
James Jean is a Taiwanese-American artist known for his mesmerizing and intricately detailed illustrations, paintings, and art book covers.

His style can be described as ethereal, fantastical, and highly imaginative. Jean's artwork often features a blend of organic and surreal elements, combining human figures, animals, and intricate patterns into visually captivating compositions.

He is celebrated for his mastery of color and texture, using a rich and vibrant palette to create depth and atmosphere in his artwork. Jean's attention to detail is remarkable, as he meticulously renders every intricate line and texture, resulting in stunning and visually complex pieces.

Jean's work encompasses a wide range of themes, including mythology, fantasy, and the human experience. His illustrations often evoke a sense of wonder and mystery, inviting viewers to delve into fantastical worlds and narratives.

In addition to his personal work, Jean has collaborated with various clients, including book publishers, fashion brands, and musicians. He has produced stunning art book covers, album artwork, and even designed the visual identity for the film "Princess Mononoke."

James Jean's art has received numerous awards and accolades, and his work has been exhibited in galleries around the world. His ability to create enchanting and evocative visuals has garnered him a devoted following and has made him one of the most influential contemporary artists.

Whether through his illustrations, paintings, or collaborations, James Jean continues to captivate audiences with his unique artistic vision and his ability to transport viewers into a world of imagination and beauty.

items.name: Tune - Style
items.description:
Did you know that not all my LoRAs are hosted on CivitAI? Check out my Patreon to learn more!

What's this LoRA

This is a LoRA trained on commissioned pictures from a user on DeviantArt. It has a nice western cartoon style with a bias towards smaller body types.

My models are not trained to achieve the exact style of their source, but to change the general vibe of the image. They are also fine-tuned on anime models, so they may not work perfectly with realistic ones.

The images in the examples are created using only this LoRA and different models (mainly my custom):

  • https://civitai.com/models/24149

  • https://civitai.com/models/26332

  • https://civitai.com/models/28322

  • https://civitai.com/models/32022

  • https://civitai.com/models/33707

You don't need to specify a word to trigger this LoRA.

What's this trained on

This LoRA was trained on pictures commissioned by a user on DeviantArt. The pictures were generated using a mixture of my Mistoon_Ruby model and some of mine + 3rd party LoRAs.

Here's a sneak peek of the dataset for those of you who wants to get an idea of what to expect from the model:

Tips for this LoRA

  • For the pictures in the examples I've used a weight of 0.5, but even with a high value I've not seen much distortion

  • This LoRA works very well with my Sapphire and Anime models. I really like the aesthetic when used with the Sapphire model.

Guides

IF YOU ARE NEW TO STABLE DIFFUSION OR YOU HAVE PROBLEMS WITH MY MODELS, GO HERE: Guide

Learn how to create pictures like mine with my step-by-step tutorials:

  • Beginner's Guide

  • Prompting

  • My Workflow

  • Inpainting

  • My Workflow

  • Tips and Tricks

If you want to create images with a high LoRA weight, I highly suggest you to check the tutorial.

Support My Work

If you want, you can support my work in different ways:

  • Check out my Patreon for exclusive content (early access to my models and exclusive polls): https://www.patreon.com/Inzaniak

  • Do you want a custom LoRA or picture? Check out my commission page: LoRA and Picture Commissions

  • If you want to support my work for free, you can also check out my music/art here:

    • Bandcamp
